# REST Client (VS Code: humao.rest-client) / IntelliJ HTTP Client
# 1) Start: uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000
# 2) Run "Get Google OAuth URL", open `url` in a browser, complete sign-in
# 3) Copy `user_id` from the callback JSON into @userId below
# 4) Run "List emails", copy a message `id` into @messageId
# 5) Run "Generate mock draft", copy `id` into @draftId, then approve and send

@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:8000
@api = {{baseUrl}}/api/v1
@userId = 72bb2df1-e9bb-4d6f-82b1-2b5deec74cca
@messageId = GMAIL_MESSAGE_ID
@draftId = DRAFT_UUID
@idempotencyKey = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001

### Root (links)
GET {{baseUrl}}/
Accept: application/json

### Health
GET {{api}}/health
Accept: application/json

### Google OAuth — get authorization URL (open `url` in browser)
# @name oauthUrl
GET {{api}}/auth/google
Accept: application/json

### Google OAuth — callback (browser hits this; usually you do NOT call manually)
# If testing manually, you need real `code` and `state` from Google redirect
# @name oauthCallback
# GET {{api}}/auth/google/callback?code=PASTE_CODE&state=PASTE_STATE
# Accept: application/json

### Auth — Gmail token health
GET {{api}}/auth/gmail/health
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
Accept: application/json

### Auth — revoke (logout + clear local tokens)
POST {{api}}/auth/revoke
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
Accept: application/json

### Emails — list (unread | recent | all)
GET {{api}}/emails?filter=unread&max_results=20
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
Accept: application/json

### Emails — list recent
GET {{api}}/emails?filter=recent&max_results=10
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
Accept: application/json

### Emails — get one message
GET {{api}}/emails/{{messageId}}
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
Accept: application/json

### Preferences — get
GET {{api}}/preferences
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
Accept: application/json

### Preferences — update (encrypted at rest)
PUT {{api}}/preferences
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "default_tone": "concise",
  "email_signature": "— You\n",
  "other": null
}

### Drafts — generate (mock LLM)
POST {{api}}/drafts/generate
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "source_message_id": "{{messageId}}",
  "tone": "concise",
  "custom_instructions": null
}

### Drafts — list
GET {{api}}/drafts?limit=50
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
Accept: application/json

### Drafts — list pending_review only
GET {{api}}/drafts?status=pending_review&limit=20
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
Accept: application/json

### Drafts — get one
GET {{api}}/drafts/{{draftId}}
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
Accept: application/json

### Drafts — edit body (only pending_review)
PATCH {{api}}/drafts/{{draftId}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "body": "Updated mock reply text.",
  "subject": null
}

### Drafts — approve
POST {{api}}/drafts/{{draftId}}/approve
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
Accept: application/json

### Drafts — reject
# POST {{api}}/drafts/{{draftId}}/reject
# X-User-Id: {{userId}}
# Accept: application/json

### Replies — send approved draft (idempotent)
POST {{api}}/replies/send
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
Idempotency-Key: {{idempotencyKey}}

{
  "draft_id": "{{draftId}}"
}

### Replies — send (same idempotency key = same result, no duplicate send)
# POST {{api}}/replies/send
# Content-Type: application/json
# X-User-Id: {{userId}}
# Idempotency-Key: {{idempotencyKey}}
#
# {
#   "draft_id": "{{draftId}}"
# }

### Audit logs
GET {{api}}/logs/audit?limit=50
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
Accept: application/json

### Audit logs — filter by event
# GET {{api}}/logs/audit?event=draft.created&limit=20
# X-User-Id: {{userId}}
# Accept: application/json
